00:00:20.877 --> 00:00:21.960
PROFESSOR: Good afternoon.

00:00:24.800 --> 00:00:28.530
We have talked in the last
class about magnetic trapping.

00:00:28.530 --> 00:00:31.910
Today, I want to finish our
discussion on magnetic traps

00:00:31.910 --> 00:00:36.300
with two demonstrations
of classical forms

00:00:36.300 --> 00:00:37.880
of magnetic trapping.

00:00:37.880 --> 00:00:39.590
But I told you that
magnetic trapping

00:00:39.590 --> 00:00:42.010
is a purely
classical phenomenon.

00:00:42.010 --> 00:00:44.490
The only quantum
mechanical aspect

00:00:44.490 --> 00:00:51.030
is that this angle at which
the magnetic dipole is oriented

00:00:51.030 --> 00:00:55.370
with the magnetic
field is quantized.

00:00:55.370 --> 00:00:57.785
I also mentioned
to you, and this

00:00:57.785 --> 00:01:01.620
was Wilks' Theorem, that
the total magnetic field can

00:01:01.620 --> 00:01:05.150
have only local
minima, not maxima.

00:01:05.150 --> 00:01:10.540
And therefore, we you can
do magnetic trapping only

00:01:10.540 --> 00:01:12.570
for weak field seeking states.

00:01:12.570 --> 00:01:17.170
These are states which
lower their energy

00:01:17.170 --> 00:01:19.370
with photomagnetic fields.

00:01:19.370 --> 00:01:22.020
And as a result,
since the spin is up,

00:01:22.020 --> 00:01:25.090
the magnetic moment
is anti-parallel

00:01:25.090 --> 00:01:27.440
to the magnetic
field, those states

00:01:27.440 --> 00:01:32.240
can always lower their
energy by flipping the spin.

00:01:32.240 --> 00:01:34.650
I know it's a simple
demonstration,

00:01:34.650 --> 00:01:37.980
but, well, I can't bring
a real magnetic trap

00:01:37.980 --> 00:01:39.450
into the classroom.

00:01:39.450 --> 00:01:42.320
So what I have here, this is
just two little ring magnets,

00:01:42.320 --> 00:01:44.570
refrigerator magnets.

00:01:44.570 --> 00:01:47.430
And there is a tube.

00:01:47.430 --> 00:01:50.520
So I just want to demonstrate
the one dimensional

00:01:50.520 --> 00:01:52.980
form of magnetic
trapping to you.

00:01:52.980 --> 00:01:54.160
And this is our atom.

00:01:54.160 --> 00:01:58.550
It's in strong
magnet, elongated,

00:01:58.550 --> 00:02:04.510
and it can be spin up
or it can be spin down.

00:02:04.510 --> 00:02:09.370
So what you're seeing is now
you're seeing the two magnets.

00:02:09.370 --> 00:02:15.780
And you're seeing
our dipole, our atom,

00:02:15.780 --> 00:02:18.070
which is in a stable
trapping configuration.

00:02:22.360 --> 00:02:24.910
And you can-- am I blocking it?

00:02:24.910 --> 00:02:31.210
You can see that it's
stable by-- I just move it.

00:02:31.210 --> 00:02:34.320
And you see how it
always comes back.

00:02:34.320 --> 00:02:35.780
So that's one position.

00:02:35.780 --> 00:02:37.630
I pull it over.

00:02:37.630 --> 00:02:43.350
Here, you have a second position
where our magnet is trapped.

00:02:43.350 --> 00:02:46.260
Here is a third one.

00:02:46.260 --> 00:02:48.110
And here's a fourth one.

00:02:48.110 --> 00:02:49.880
So there are four
positions where

00:02:49.880 --> 00:02:52.570
we have one
dimensional trapping.

00:02:52.570 --> 00:02:55.410
Well, this is one
for one orientation.

00:02:55.410 --> 00:02:59.330
Now I take the magnet
and flip it over.

00:02:59.330 --> 00:03:02.680
So we are changing now
in the laboratory frame.

00:03:02.680 --> 00:03:05.830
The sign of the magnetic moment.

00:03:05.830 --> 00:03:08.270
And there is actually
a very nice minimum.

00:03:08.270 --> 00:03:12.580
You see how clearly
it is trapped.

00:03:12.580 --> 00:03:16.110
There is one here in the middle.

00:03:16.110 --> 00:03:18.920
I can also just show
you, it really stays put.

00:03:18.920 --> 00:03:20.870
There's a weak restoring force.

00:03:20.870 --> 00:03:23.720
And then here's number three.

00:03:23.720 --> 00:03:25.400
So it seems very, very rich.

00:03:25.400 --> 00:03:29.000
I've shown you seven
different minima

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:31.400
where trapping has happened.

00:03:31.400 --> 00:03:36.020
And well, just to fill you
in, if this is our magnet,

00:03:36.020 --> 00:03:38.350
these are ring magnets,
the magnetic field

00:03:38.350 --> 00:03:41.560
is about something like that.

00:03:41.560 --> 00:03:47.950
And if I plot the magnetic
field for this configuration,

00:03:47.950 --> 00:03:56.270
I find indeed that
for one orientation,

00:03:56.270 --> 00:04:00.520
there are four maxima.

00:04:00.520 --> 00:04:06.040
So for one orientation--
just give me one second.

00:04:19.550 --> 00:04:22.870
Yeah, there are four maxima
of the magnetic field

00:04:22.870 --> 00:04:24.710
for this orientation.

00:04:24.710 --> 00:04:26.360
And therefore, there
are four minima

00:04:26.360 --> 00:04:29.820
of the trapping potential.

00:04:29.820 --> 00:04:32.110
So maybe I should have
shown it like this.

00:04:32.110 --> 00:04:35.110
There are one, two,
three, four minima.

00:04:35.110 --> 00:04:40.530
And for the opposite
configuration,

00:04:40.530 --> 00:04:44.300
there are one, two,
three trapping minima.

00:04:44.300 --> 00:04:48.090
But now if you look, there are
one, two, three, four, five,

00:04:48.090 --> 00:04:52.870
six ones marked in red, which
are for strong field seekers,

00:04:52.870 --> 00:04:56.240
because these are maxima
at the magnetic field.

00:04:56.240 --> 00:04:58.170
And there is only one
where the magnetic field

00:04:58.170 --> 00:05:00.260
has a local minimum.

00:05:00.260 --> 00:05:03.140
So in the last
part, I have shown

00:05:03.140 --> 00:05:08.250
you the absolute value
of the magnetic field.

00:05:08.250 --> 00:05:11.070
And you realize there are
one, two, three, four, five,

00:05:11.070 --> 00:05:12.340
six maxima.

00:05:12.340 --> 00:05:15.440
And this is responsible for
six trapping configurations.

00:05:15.440 --> 00:05:19.230
And the seventh one was a
minimum of the magnetic field.

00:05:19.230 --> 00:05:21.450
So in one dimension,
there is no problem.

00:05:21.450 --> 00:05:24.070
In one dimension, I can
get a restoring force

00:05:24.070 --> 00:05:26.880
for the strong and for
the weak field seeker

00:05:26.880 --> 00:05:29.540
for any orientation of
the magnetic dipole.

00:05:29.540 --> 00:05:32.820
But if we want to have a
three dimensional trap,

00:05:32.820 --> 00:05:37.860
we have to look at the
three dimensional stability.

00:05:37.860 --> 00:05:42.240
And it would be only
this one configuration,

00:05:42.240 --> 00:05:45.700
which can be
stabilised in x and y.

00:05:45.700 --> 00:05:47.950
What I've shown you
are symmetric fields.

00:05:47.950 --> 00:05:51.190
So all these minima and
maxima only settle points.

00:05:51.190 --> 00:05:52.950
They trap in one dimension.

00:05:52.950 --> 00:05:56.190
But with suitable
radial magnetic field,

00:05:56.190 --> 00:06:00.040
you could turn this one
here into a real three

00:06:00.040 --> 00:06:01.210
dimensional trap.

00:06:01.210 --> 00:06:04.840
But the other ones you cannot,
because this would violate

00:06:04.840 --> 00:06:05.610
Wilks' Theorem.

00:06:11.690 --> 00:06:14.900
I find it amazing that
this demonstration

00:06:14.900 --> 00:06:19.550
has seven different magnetic
trapping configurations.

00:06:19.550 --> 00:06:21.460
That's just how it
turns out to be.

00:06:21.460 --> 00:06:24.130
Questions?

00:06:24.130 --> 00:06:25.046
Collin.

00:06:25.046 --> 00:06:26.837
AUDIENCE: So if you
look at the clover leaf

00:06:26.837 --> 00:06:35.846
coil, the parts of the field
that sort of axial [INAUDIBLE]

00:06:35.846 --> 00:06:39.270
provided by [INAUDIBLE],
those are the inner coils?

00:06:39.270 --> 00:06:42.110
PROFESSOR: Yeah, so if you
look at a clover leaf trap,

00:06:42.110 --> 00:06:44.730
the pinch coils
create such a minimum,

00:06:44.730 --> 00:06:48.020
which provides confinement
in the z direction.

00:06:48.020 --> 00:06:52.750
But then you add a field, a
radially outward quadrupole

00:06:52.750 --> 00:06:59.745
field, and that overcomes--
in this demonstration,

00:06:59.745 --> 00:07:01.120
everything is
actually symmetric.

00:07:01.120 --> 00:07:04.040
So this is a minimum
for this direction.

00:07:04.040 --> 00:07:08.140
But if you would now plot it
as a function of x and y and z,

00:07:08.140 --> 00:07:09.760
it would be a saddle point.

00:07:09.760 --> 00:07:12.800
So this configuration
is trapping along z,

00:07:12.800 --> 00:07:15.600
but anti-trapping along x and y.

00:07:15.600 --> 00:07:17.450
But if you add a
quadrupole field,

00:07:17.450 --> 00:07:20.470
a linear field which points
outward with these clover

00:07:20.470 --> 00:07:24.720
leaves or the [INAUDIBLE]
bars, then they

00:07:24.720 --> 00:07:27.960
would provide confinement,
which is stronger

00:07:27.960 --> 00:07:30.840
than the anti-confinement
of the saddle point.

00:07:30.840 --> 00:07:33.580
If you look at some equations
I showed you in the last class,

00:07:33.580 --> 00:07:36.940
you will actually see
that in one of the slides,

00:07:36.940 --> 00:07:39.860
I had the expression
for the magnetic field,

00:07:39.860 --> 00:07:43.050
where you see how
the [INAUDIBLE] bars,

00:07:43.050 --> 00:07:46.930
the radially linear
confinement overcomes

00:07:46.930 --> 00:07:53.230
the anti-trapping feature
of the settle point.

00:07:53.230 --> 00:07:53.920
Other question?

00:07:56.860 --> 00:08:03.360
Then finally, let me give you a
demonstration for the following

00:08:03.360 --> 00:08:05.940
effect.

00:08:05.940 --> 00:08:10.600
I mentioned to you that
magnetic traps become unstable

00:08:10.600 --> 00:08:13.830
when the magnetic
field is very low.

00:08:13.830 --> 00:08:16.360
And I told you, well, at
very low magnetic field,

00:08:16.360 --> 00:08:18.810
the energy difference
between spin up and spin down

00:08:18.810 --> 00:08:20.350
is very small.

00:08:20.350 --> 00:08:22.900
At zero magnetic
field, it becomes zero.

00:08:22.900 --> 00:08:28.320
And then, the atom cannot
adiabatically stay in its MF

00:08:28.320 --> 00:08:33.970
state, because we can violate
the adiabaticity condition.

00:08:33.970 --> 00:08:36.850
So let me now show you
an example of purely

00:08:36.850 --> 00:08:38.659
classical trapping.

00:08:38.659 --> 00:08:42.690
And I think a number of you
now have seen the levitron toy.

00:08:42.690 --> 00:08:48.340
Actually, a few years ago when
my group was one of the first

00:08:48.340 --> 00:08:50.900
to use magnetic trapping,
in every single talk

00:08:50.900 --> 00:08:53.150
I explained how
magnetic trap worked.

00:08:53.150 --> 00:08:56.050
And I even showed this
demonstration live.

00:08:56.050 --> 00:08:58.470
But in order to
demonstrate it really well,

00:08:58.470 --> 00:09:00.460
I was building my own levitron.

00:09:00.460 --> 00:09:01.950
I used machine parts.

00:09:01.950 --> 00:09:03.490
I used the motor drive.

00:09:03.490 --> 00:09:05.970
So I hope I can show you
one aspect of the levitron

00:09:05.970 --> 00:09:12.010
demonstration, which
is usually not known.

00:09:12.010 --> 00:09:15.880
So let me first give
you the punchline.

00:09:15.880 --> 00:09:20.020
Magnetic trapping happens
with an orientation

00:09:20.020 --> 00:09:23.810
of the magnetic dipole
which could always

00:09:23.810 --> 00:09:26.230
lower its energy
by flipping over.

00:09:26.230 --> 00:09:29.140
The reason why it
doesn't flip over-- well,

00:09:29.140 --> 00:09:30.770
quantum mechanically,
it adiabatically

00:09:30.770 --> 00:09:33.920
stays in a quantum
state-- but classically,

00:09:33.920 --> 00:09:37.920
if we have angular momentum, it
is gyroscopically stabilized.

00:09:37.920 --> 00:09:42.220
The dipole cannot flip over,
because it's a gyroscope.

00:09:42.220 --> 00:09:43.950
It has angular momentum.

00:09:43.950 --> 00:09:45.750
And actually, it also
has angular momentum

00:09:45.750 --> 00:09:46.610
in quantum physics.

00:09:46.610 --> 00:09:49.650
So the two explanations
sounded different

00:09:49.650 --> 00:09:52.290
when I said stays
in a quantum state,

00:09:52.290 --> 00:09:53.800
is gyroscopically stabilized.

00:09:53.800 --> 00:09:56.220
But if you think
about it more deeply,

00:09:56.220 --> 00:09:59.440
they have much more in common
than my language suggests.

00:09:59.440 --> 00:10:03.190
So I think you know
how the levitron works.

00:10:03.190 --> 00:10:05.250
You spin up the magnet.

00:10:05.250 --> 00:10:08.890
And I had this nice
motor tool to spin it up.

00:10:08.890 --> 00:10:11.220
And when you have
prepared the system.

00:10:11.220 --> 00:10:13.940
Your atom has now-- atom in
quotes-- angular momentum

00:10:13.940 --> 00:10:15.170
in the magnetic moment.

00:10:15.170 --> 00:10:18.870
And you bring it to the position
where the three dimensional

00:10:18.870 --> 00:10:22.630
magnetic field fulfills
the stability condition.

00:10:22.630 --> 00:10:25.380
And you can now enjoy
magnetic trapping.

00:10:25.380 --> 00:10:29.830
This is exactly what your
atoms do in your magnetic trap.

00:10:29.830 --> 00:10:33.415
It is gyroscopically
stabilized magnetic levitation.

00:10:36.640 --> 00:10:40.020
The only difference is that
gravity has to be compensated.

00:10:40.020 --> 00:10:41.770
Gravity is a major player.

00:10:41.770 --> 00:10:45.040
So the stability point
in the three dimensional

00:10:45.040 --> 00:10:49.440
magnetic field configuration
includes the compensation

00:10:49.440 --> 00:10:51.040
for gravity.

00:10:51.040 --> 00:10:53.250
But I have to say, my group
was also at some point

00:10:53.250 --> 00:10:56.430
trapping a Bose-Einstein
condensate in a few hertz

00:10:56.430 --> 00:11:00.450
weak trap, where gravity was
the strongest force of all.

00:11:00.450 --> 00:11:04.990
So what you have seen is
an exact demonstration

00:11:04.990 --> 00:11:08.800
of the principle for
magnetic trapping.

00:11:08.800 --> 00:11:10.490
But now comes my question.

00:11:10.490 --> 00:11:12.440
What would you
expect, what would

00:11:12.440 --> 00:11:19.070
happen to our magnetic trap when
we spin the levitron faster?

00:11:19.070 --> 00:11:23.860
Does it help or does it hurt to
spin up the levitron, to spin

00:11:23.860 --> 00:11:26.800
up the gyroscope, to
higher angular velocities?

00:11:30.490 --> 00:11:31.790
So three possibility.

00:11:31.790 --> 00:11:32.480
Nothing happens.

00:11:32.480 --> 00:11:34.670
It doesn't matter
as long as it spins.

00:11:34.670 --> 00:11:38.070
The second one, the trap
becomes more stable.

00:11:38.070 --> 00:11:42.590
The third possibility,
the trap becomes unstable.

00:11:42.590 --> 00:11:44.560
Do you want to
offer any opinion?

00:12:00.110 --> 00:12:00.636
Collin.

00:12:00.636 --> 00:12:02.760
AUDIENCE: Well, we have an
angular momentum, right,

00:12:02.760 --> 00:12:05.636
of the really large omega.

00:12:05.636 --> 00:12:07.548
When you apply
torque, it's going

00:12:07.548 --> 00:12:09.938
to get torque
[INAUDIBLE], right.

00:12:09.938 --> 00:12:11.850
It's going to be the
prefactor of omega.

00:12:11.850 --> 00:12:17.389
So we have a giant omega, we
imagine that [INAUDIBLE] small,

00:12:17.389 --> 00:12:18.383
[INAUDIBLE] torques.

00:12:21.318 --> 00:12:22.359
No, no, no wait a second.

00:12:22.359 --> 00:12:23.400
I did this the other way.

00:12:23.400 --> 00:12:26.350
It was [? healing. ?]
Never mind.

00:12:26.350 --> 00:12:28.750
PROFESSOR: So do we have
to do the experiment?

00:12:28.750 --> 00:12:30.680
Maybe.

00:12:30.680 --> 00:12:32.900
So now I put the motor
controller to full speed.

00:12:32.900 --> 00:12:34.830
And I speed it up much faster.

00:12:34.830 --> 00:12:36.672
You can hear the sound.

00:12:36.672 --> 00:12:38.380
I really want to do
a careful experiment.

00:12:38.380 --> 00:12:41.830
So we wait until everything
is quiet and has died out.

00:12:41.830 --> 00:12:45.100
And now, we want to try if we
can can do magnetic trapping.

00:12:45.100 --> 00:12:46.920
And you see it's impossible.

00:12:46.920 --> 00:12:49.060
The system, when it
reaches the point where

00:12:49.060 --> 00:12:52.840
magnetic trapping would
occur, it's unstable.

00:12:52.840 --> 00:12:55.230
But then, well, just to
prove that it is only

00:12:55.230 --> 00:12:58.420
the speed of rotation which
has caused the instability,

00:12:58.420 --> 00:13:01.370
I just wait until
friction has slowed down

00:13:01.370 --> 00:13:02.800
the angular velocity.

00:13:02.800 --> 00:13:05.040
And now again, it
works perfectly.

00:13:07.860 --> 00:13:14.860
So you see, if you rotate the
gyroscope too fast, it's bad.

00:13:14.860 --> 00:13:16.850
It makes the magnetic
trap unstable.

00:13:19.720 --> 00:13:21.340
Convinced?

00:13:21.340 --> 00:13:22.560
How would you explain that?

00:13:41.660 --> 00:13:44.020
If we have a gyro-- Collin?

00:13:44.020 --> 00:13:46.520
AUDIENCE: Why aren't we working
in the limit where we assume

00:13:46.520 --> 00:13:50.885
that the magnetic field
generated by our magnet

00:13:50.885 --> 00:13:53.795
is sort of weak
compared to the trap.

00:13:53.795 --> 00:13:57.700
So the magnet's really
modifying [INAUDIBLE].

00:13:57.700 --> 00:13:59.700
PROFESSOR: No, we
assume here-- and I

00:13:59.700 --> 00:14:01.660
can give you the
analysis-- but yes.

00:14:01.660 --> 00:14:03.320
No, these are permanent magnets.

00:14:03.320 --> 00:14:08.400
So the floating magnet is just,
you can say, a probe, a test

00:14:08.400 --> 00:14:12.760
object which is put into
the permanent magnetic field

00:14:12.760 --> 00:14:16.458
of the stronger magnets
of the stationary magnet.

00:14:16.458 --> 00:14:19.452
AUDIENCE: Get an
additional torque

00:14:19.452 --> 00:14:22.446
to-- because it gets
an additional force

00:14:22.446 --> 00:14:23.943
into the upper state.

00:14:23.943 --> 00:14:27.935
So it gets an additional
torque in towards the center.

00:14:30.940 --> 00:14:35.069
PROFESSOR: It's not necessarily
the additional torque.

00:14:35.069 --> 00:14:37.360
Let's put two things together,
it's really fascinating,

00:14:37.360 --> 00:14:38.780
from different principles.

00:14:38.780 --> 00:14:45.070
The first thing is
magnetic trapping

00:14:45.070 --> 00:14:47.586
requires-- if you
have a magnetic trap

00:14:47.586 --> 00:14:49.460
and you have an
inhomogeneous magnetic field.

00:14:49.460 --> 00:14:52.100
And of course, you need an
inhomogeneous magnetic field,

00:14:52.100 --> 00:14:55.810
the angle cosine theta
between the spinning dipole

00:14:55.810 --> 00:14:59.240
and the magnetic field
should stay the same.

00:14:59.240 --> 00:15:01.190
And this means
quantum mechanically,

00:15:01.190 --> 00:15:02.990
we stay in the
same quantum state.

00:15:02.990 --> 00:15:04.900
So therefore, a
magnetic trap only

00:15:04.900 --> 00:15:09.560
works because the
rapidly precessing spin,

00:15:09.560 --> 00:15:12.430
when the magnetic
field always precesses

00:15:12.430 --> 00:15:13.770
around the magnetic field.

00:15:13.770 --> 00:15:15.930
And when the
magnetic field tips,

00:15:15.930 --> 00:15:21.170
the precession keeps the
dipole, the magnetic moment,

00:15:21.170 --> 00:15:23.520
aligned with the magnetic field.

00:15:23.520 --> 00:15:27.380
Now, what happens in a gyroscope
with a precession frequency

00:15:27.380 --> 00:15:29.160
when you spin the
gyroscope faster?

